33:56.077 --> 34:00.386
♪ Come on, Johnny, please

34:00.429 --> 34:06.305
♪ Won't you speak to me?

34:06.348 --> 34:08.655
♪ Ooh, ooh

34:08.698 --> 34:10.700
♪ Ooh

34:10.744 --> 34:13.094
- Ready to restart the heart.

34:13.138 --> 34:14.226
- Everything's solid.

34:14.269 --> 34:16.271
- Charging.
Clear.

34:16.315 --> 34:17.838
- Suctioning.

34:21.668 --> 34:23.670
- Quarter's ready.

34:23.713 --> 34:27.500
[tense music]

34:27.543 --> 34:30.459
[machine beeping]

34:30.503 --> 34:33.288
- We did it.

34:33.332 --> 34:35.116
- Good job, everyone.

34:35.160 --> 34:38.511
[warm music]

34:38.554 --> 34:40.469
- [sighs]

34:40.513 --> 34:41.775
Ooh.

34:41.818 --> 34:43.994
- All right,
let's close him up.

34:44.038 --> 34:50.044
♪

34:50.088 --> 34:52.002
[machine beeping rapidly]
BP is dropping.

34:52.046 --> 34:53.221
- What?

34:53.265 --> 34:54.962
- Heart valve's not holding.
- It's slipping.

34:55.005 --> 34:56.572
Give me a 3-0 proline
on the needle driver.

34:56.616 --> 34:58.139
- Times two.

34:58.183 --> 35:01.534
- You work the septum,
I'll work the free wall.

35:01.577 --> 35:03.144
I'm gonna have to get him
back on bypass.

35:03.188 --> 35:04.885
- We can't reestablish
aortic cannulation.

35:04.928 --> 35:07.148
- [grunts]
- As a backup, yes.

35:08.889 --> 35:10.586
- My stitches aren't holding.
- Neither are mine.

35:10.630 --> 35:11.935
- Trying 5-0.
- Suction needs to be higher.

35:11.979 --> 35:13.546
- I'm not getting any purchase.

35:13.589 --> 35:15.461
- Another bag.

35:15.504 --> 35:17.289
- Come on.
Hold, damn it.

35:17.332 --> 35:18.899
- Flash sterilized.

35:21.467 --> 35:24.426
[somber music]

35:24.470 --> 35:31.564
♪

35:36.090 --> 35:37.744
- Ansuya.

35:37.787 --> 35:40.877
[ethereal music]

35:41.965 --> 35:44.054
Ansuya.

35:48.755 --> 35:55.892
- ♪ Oh

35:56.806 --> 36:00.462
♪ Oh

36:00.506 --> 36:05.206
♪ Oh, oh

36:05.250 --> 36:07.991
- Ansuya.

36:09.341 --> 36:11.430
- Vijay.

36:11.473 --> 36:18.567
- ♪ Oh, oh, oh

36:28.577 --> 36:30.318
- Eat this.

36:32.668 --> 36:35.062
- I don't need it.

36:37.238 --> 36:40.023
All I need is you.

36:40.067 --> 36:42.504
- It will give you strength

36:42.548 --> 36:45.551
for our granddaughter.

36:45.594 --> 36:46.943
- Granddaughter?
[laughs]

36:46.987 --> 36:49.511
- She needs her Dadaji.

36:49.555 --> 36:56.692
- ♪ Oh

36:57.476 --> 37:03.873
♪ Oh

37:05.310 --> 37:12.230
♪ Oh

37:13.579 --> 37:15.711
- Vijay?

37:17.713 --> 37:20.803
- ♪ Ah

37:23.458 --> 37:26.418
[machine beeping]

37:26.461 --> 37:28.289
- He's waking up.

37:28.333 --> 37:29.856
Oh, thank God.
Vijay.

37:29.899 --> 37:31.510
[warm music]

37:31.553 --> 37:33.468
- Welcome back, Dr. Kapoor.

37:33.512 --> 37:40.562
♪

37:40.823 --> 37:42.738
- [chuckles]

37:42.782 --> 37:44.262
[sighs]

37:47.352 --> 37:50.180
[baby crying]

38:03.368 --> 38:06.458
- [laughs]
Happy birthday, little one.

38:06.501 --> 38:08.286
[both laughing]

38:08.329 --> 38:11.245
[baby cooing]

38:14.683 --> 38:16.903
- Uh, K-Karen!

38:16.946 --> 38:19.340
- Are the cops chasing you now?
- Uh, I don't know,

38:19.384 --> 38:21.777
but I did come up with a solve
for our opioid issue,

38:21.821 --> 38:23.388
and I think you're really
gonna like it.

38:23.431 --> 38:24.954
- And here I thought
we knew each other better.

38:24.998 --> 38:26.608
- Watermarking.

38:26.652 --> 38:30.308
So every single opioid
that New Amsterdam sends out

38:30.351 --> 38:31.787
into the world
will be watermarked

38:31.831 --> 38:34.660
with invisible,
fluorescent fibers.

38:34.703 --> 38:36.966
Every patient will have access

38:37.010 --> 38:39.621
to the medicine they need
and without shame.

38:39.665 --> 38:42.581
And they'll be able
to manage their pain,

38:42.624 --> 38:45.975
and they'll be able to live
functional lives.

38:46.019 --> 38:48.195
But if those pills ever do
end up in the street,

38:48.238 --> 38:49.892
or in the wrong hands,
we'll know.

38:49.936 --> 38:52.808
There will be
no drug trafficking,

38:52.852 --> 38:56.421
and there will
be accountability.

38:57.987 --> 38:59.815
Oh, and I almost forgot
the best part.

38:59.859 --> 39:02.818
The Nylers are gonna
pay for it.

39:02.862 --> 39:04.429
- Why would they do that?

39:04.472 --> 39:06.213
- They kinda have to.

39:06.256 --> 39:07.606
Part of their settlement
includes

39:07.649 --> 39:10.304
donating millions of dollars
to public hospitals,

39:10.348 --> 39:11.653
just like ours.

39:11.697 --> 39:13.089
- [laughs]

39:13.133 --> 39:15.222
I don't know what to say.

39:15.265 --> 39:17.355
It sounds like
a well-thought-out

39:17.398 --> 39:18.747
and realistic plan.

39:18.791 --> 39:20.488
- I know.
Weird, right?

39:20.532 --> 39:22.229
- [chuckles]

39:22.272 --> 39:24.971
- Karen.

39:25.014 --> 39:28.409
Thank you
for keeping me accountable.

39:28.453 --> 39:30.193
- That's my job.

39:32.021 --> 39:35.242
And every once and a while,
it's worth it.

39:41.596 --> 39:44.512
[keys clacking]

39:58.874 --> 40:01.442
- I'm not ready.

40:03.313 --> 40:04.967
- Okay.

40:07.796 --> 40:11.887
- I mean,
I'm not ready to call it.

40:25.945 --> 40:28.861
[hopeful music]

40:28.904 --> 40:36.042
♪

40:55.061 --> 40:58.020
[somber music]

40:58.064 --> 41:05.201
♪

41:52.597 --> 41:55.904
- I should've been here.

41:55.948 --> 41:58.428
- Well, you're here now.

42:47.260 --> 42:49.218
[thunder rumbling]

42:49.262 --> 42:51.351
[projector clicking]
